<!--

source= http://kidoyo.com/htmllesson.php

This is a lesson for the beginner++ getting familiar with html/css/javascript code. In this lesson, you will be building a web page. The style of this page allows for you to create a comic strip. It is also useful for remixing, so that you can change the style and use the page for a purpose other than a comic strip. In this lesson, you are working on a code farm, and different scenes will involve different challenges, taking you through a learning journey exploring multiple web publishing ideas. This lesson will cover:

        - Changing images
        - Changing text
        - Changing classes
        - Copying nodes
        - Embedding scripts
        - Adding hyperlinks
        - More++

-->

<!--

    1) READ THROUGH COMMENTS. This is a comment. Everything inside of this html tag or '/*' tag for CSS, is not processed as code. Instead it works as text comments about the code you write. Good code is commented code. As you work on this project, comments will give you instructions, hints and guides for completing the project. You can also write your own comments about your project. Read ahead and try it out.

    2) Learn about CODE. <html> is made up of tags that look like this <p> </p>. The tags tell you something about the information contained between them. Click on the tags in the code on this side of the editor to get a description of what each tag is for.
  -->    
    
    <title>kidOYO Webmaker Code Farm</title>

